messages.content: What is the purpose of the Oobabooga Node in Xycuno-Oobabooga?
The Oobabooga Node is a custom node added to Xycuno-Oobabooga in its initial release.
When was the initial release of Xycuno-Oobabooga?
The initial release of Xycuno-Oobabooga was on 2024-03-12.
What was the version number of the initial release of Xycuno-Oobabooga?
The version number of the initial release of Xycuno-Oobabooga was 0.0.0.
Does Xycuno-Oobabooga follow any specific versioning system?
Yes, Xycuno-Oobabooga adheres to Semantic Versioning as specified in https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html.
Is the format of the changelog in Xycuno-Oobabooga based on any specific style?
Yes, the format of the changelog in Xycuno-Oobabooga is based on Keep a Changelog as specified in https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/.
What is the current version of Xycuno-Oobabooga?
The current version of Xycuno-Oobabooga is 0.0.0.
What are the notable changes documented in the changelog for version 0.0.0 of Xycuno-Oobabooga?
The notable change documented in the changelog for version 0.0.0 of Xycuno-Oobabooga is the addition of the Oobabooga Node.
How can I install Xycuno-Oobabooga for ComfyUI?

You can install Xycuno-Oobabooga by using 'git clone' or 'git submodule'. For 'git clone', navigate to the 'custom_nodes' directory of your ComfyUI installation and use 'git clone https://github.com/Xyem/Xycuno-Oobabooga.git'. For 'git submodule', you can add it using 'git submodule add -f https://github.com/Xyem/Xycuno-Oobabooga.git xycuno_oobabooga'.
What is the purpose of the Oobabooga node in Xycuno-Oobabooga?
The Oobabooga node in Xycuno-Oobabooga is used for having Oobabooga complete the rest of the provided text.
What is the default value for 'host' in the Oobabooga node?
The default value for 'host' in the Oobabooga node is 'http://127.0.0.1:5000'.
What is the default value for 'max_tokens' in the Oobabooga node?
The default value for 'max_tokens' in the Oobabooga node is '200'.
What does the 'response' output in the Oobabooga node represent?
The 'response' output in the Oobabooga node represents the text returned by Oobabooga, not including the 'prompt'.
What is the default value for 'temperature' in the Oobabooga node?
The default value for 'temperature' in the Oobabooga node is '1.0'.
What is the default value for 'top_p' in the Oobabooga node?
The default value for 'top_p' in the Oobabooga node is '0.9'.
